The paper deals with optimization in decentralized control problems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of deterministic annealing, a non-convex optimization framework derived from information theoretic principles, suggests that the paper may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) category. The paper also mentions the use of clustering and regression, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization and decision making, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
